    "details": {
      "en": {
        "id": "en",
        "purpose": "To estimate the risk of in hospital mortality based on comorbidities. ",
        "keywords": [
          "Comorbidity ",
          "in-hospital death",
          "Mortality"
        ],
        "use": "Formula: \nAddition of the selected points: (variables and points)\n1. Congestive heart failure: 7\n2. Cardiac arrhythmias: 5\n3. Valvular disease: -1\n4. Pulmonary circulation disorders: 4\n5. Peripheral vascular disorders: 2\n6. Hypertension: 0\n7. Paralysis: 7\n8. Neurodegenerative disorders: 6\n9. Chronic pulmonary disease: 3\n10. Diabetes: No=0, Diabetes without chronic complications=0, Diabetes with chronic complications=0\n11. Hypothyroidism: 0\n12. Renal failure: 5\n13. Liver disease: 11\n14. Peptic ulcer disease, no bleeding: 0\n15. AIDS/HIV: 0\n16. Lymphoma: 9\n19. Metastatic cancer: 12\n20. Solid tumor without metastasis: 4\n21. Rheumatoid arthritis/collagen vascular diseases: 0\n22. Coagulopathy: 3\n23. Obesity: -4\n24. Weight loss: 6\n25. Fluid and electrolyte disorders: 5\n26. Blood loss anemia: -2\n27. Deficiency anemia: -2\n28. Alcohol abuse: 0\n29. Drug abuse: -7\n30. Psychosis: 0\n31. Depressions: -3\nInterpretation: \nElixhauser Comorbidity Index score and probability of inpatient death:\n -19= 0.37%, \n>=-18 to <=10: 0.37- 2%\n>10 to <=0: 1-6%\n>0 to <=20: 6-16%\n>20 to <=30: 15-33%\n>30 to <=40: 32-57%\n>40 to <=50: 57-79%\n>50 to <=60: 79-92%\n>60 to <=70: 92-97%\n>70 to <=80: 97- 99%\n>80 to <89: 99-99.41%\n 89=99.41%, \n",
        "misuse": "",
        "copyright": "@CambioCDS"
      }
    },
    "other_details": {
      "references": "1. Elixhauser, Anne, et al. \"Comorbidity measures for use with administrative data.\" Medical care (1998): 8-27.\n2. van Walraven, Carl, et al. \"A modification of the Elixhauser comorbidity measures into a point system for hospital death using administrative data.\" Medical care (2009): 626-633.\n3. Menendez, Mariano E., et al. \"Predicting in-hospital mortality in elderly patients with cervical spine fractures: a comparison of the Charlson and Elixhauser Comorbidity Measures.\" Spine 40.11 (2015): 809-815.\n4. Menendez, Mariano E., and David Ring. \"A comparison of the Charlson and Elixhauser comorbidity measures to predict inpatient mortality after proximal humerus fracture.\" Journal of orthopaedic trauma 29.11 (2015): 488-493.\n5. Kim, Chang-Yeon, et al. \"Predicting adverse events, length of stay, and discharge disposition following shoulder arthroplasty: a comparison of the Elixhauser Comorbidity Measure and Charlson Comorbidity Index.\" Journal of Shoulder and Elbow Surgery (2018)."
    }
  },
